==English==

===Adjective===
'''keening'''

#[[sharp|Sharp]], [[shrill]], especially of a sound.
#:''The '''keening''' sound of a dentist's drill sets my teeth on edge, and I'm a dentist.''

===Etymology===
From Irish ''Caoineadh'' meaning lament.
===Noun===
'''keening'''
#Exaggerated moanful [[wailing]] at a [[funeral]] or [[wake]]
#(by extension) An [[unpleasant]] sound.